<%- include("../partials/header") %>

<!-- hero section -->
 <!-- Will add an image later (3D animation) - Charlotte -->

<div class="homepagina">
  <section>
    <h2>Find Gamers That<br>Match Your Playstyle</h1>

    <p>No random teammates. Just better matches.</p>
    <div>
      <% if (currentUser) { %>
        <a href="/dashboard">Go to dashboard</a>
        <a href="/matches">Matching</a>
      <% } else { %>
        <a href="/register">Get Started Free</a>
        <a href="/login">Log in</a>
      <% } %>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- all the benefits -->

  <section>
    <h2>Why This Changes<br>Your Gaming Experience</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <h3>Play with people matching your schedule</h3>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>Match by skill and experience</h3>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>Build real gaming friendships</h3>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>Less time searching, more time playing</h3>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>Cross-platform compatibility</h3>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>Instant availability visibility</h3>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- how the matching process works -->
    <!-- Images on each list item still needs to be added, but the text is in place for now - Charlotte -->

  <section>
    <h2>Get Matched in Seconds!</h2>
    <ul class="step-by-step">

      <li>
        <h3>1. Create Your Profile</h3>
        <p>Personalise your profile with your gaming preferences, skill level, and schedule.</p>
        <img src="/images/icon_step-1_matching.png" alt="">
      </li>

      <li>
        <h3>2. Get Matched</h3>
        <p>Our algorithm finds gamers who fit your profile and are available to play.</p>
        <img src="/images/icon_step-2_matching.png" alt="">
      </li>

      <li>
        <h3>3. Connect and Play</h3>
        <p>Chat with your matches, set up gaming sessions, and start playing together.</p>
        <img src="/images/icon_step-3_matching.png" alt="">
      </li>

    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- information section about the API and technology -->

  <section>
    <h2>Behind the Platform</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <h3>Game Data (API)</h3>
        <p>We use the RAWG API to fetch up-to-date information about games, including titles, genres, and supported platforms. This ensures that all data on the platform is accurate and consistent, so users can easily find matches based on real and current game information.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>Backend</h3>
        <p>The backend is built with Node.js and uses MongoDB to store user profiles and preferences. This allows the system to process filters and match players based on shared games, platforms, availability, and experience, creating more relevant and accurate matches.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>Frontend</h3>
        <p>The frontend is developed with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, providing a smooth and simple interface. Users can easily search, filter, and view profiles, making it simple to quickly find and connect with the right gaming partners.</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>


</div>

<%- include("../partials/footer") %>
